.TH "ecryptfs_encrypt_and_encode_filename" 9 "ecryptfs_encrypt_and_encode_filename" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ecryptfs_encrypt_and_encode_filename \- converts a plaintext file name to cipher text
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ecryptfs_encrypt_and_encode_filename
.BI "(char **encoded_name "  ","
.BI "size_t *encoded_name_size "  ","
.BI "struct ecryptfs_mount_crypt_stat *mount_crypt_stat "  ","
.BI "const char *name "  ","
.BI "size_t name_size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "encoded_name" 12
The encypted name
.IP "encoded_name_size" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "mount_crypt_stat" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "name" 12
The plaintext name
.IP "name_size" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Encrypts and encodes a filename into something that constitutes a
valid filename for a filesystem, with printable characters.

We assume that we have a properly initialized crypto context,
pointed to by crypt_stat->tfm.

Returns zero on success; non-zero on otherwise
